body:
Hiiiiiiiii 
So it&#039;s been about 3 days since this problem occurred, I&#039;ve seen other threads about it but nothing has seemed to fix the problem.
Basically every game after champ select, (normals, customs, spectating) the game crashes. It begins with a black screen at which you have to press enter, then an empty champion screen appears for a split second before immediately crashing and the reconnect button is prompted.
So far the steps I have taken in this order are: Repairing the client -&gt; Uninstalling and reinstalling League of Legends -&gt; Repairing again (idk why haha) -&gt; Forcing a repatch. Then today I upgraded my OSX from yosemite to El capitan and launching a game in custom worked. Immediately trying to play a normal after brought the whole problem back and now nothing works.

Just so you know, I don&#039;t have lolreplay or avast or any firewall or antivirus&#039; 
I&#039;ve opened a ticket a few days ago but they always ask confusing things at extended notice so if anyone has a solution I would be more than grateful :)))){{sticker:slayer-jinx-catface}}
